<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When parsing an Atom link element, the presence of an empty href attribute fails to trigger a URI construction using the base URI of the feed. Essentially an empty href attribute should be interpreted as being equal to the base URI of the feed.</p>

<p>This can be fixed by detecting relative URIs more robustly and holding the base URI of the feed as a separate cached value to simplify implementation. Some checking should be done to ascertain whether this also effects the RSS parsing class and perhaps add a getBaseUri() method to the feed and entry APIs.</p>

